stylometry: Elasticity of demand is how price directly effects the demand of a product. It states that as the price of a product goes down, the demand for the product goes up, and when the price of a product goes up, the demand for it goes down. But when you are dealing with neccessities in life (food, medicine, gas, etc.) then these products are what we call INelastic and the demand for these products does not change based on price because we need them to survive and live our lives so we will pay for them no matter what cost because we have no choice. That is why the oil companies are killing us right now.
